  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When backing up a seedphrase there's a step where the user has to confirm the #n-th word of the seedphrase:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-09-30 07-53-00](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/193200296-49f2e11a-bf8e-4a82-a57f-d18a7e81f8d1.png)\r\n\r\nDespite the screenshot showing the input being in validation mode, what happens is that the input doesn't gain focus when it enters the view.\r\nUsers are forced to click into the input to start confirming their seedphrase.\r\n\r\nThe single most important input should automatically get active focus when it enters the view.",
